Title: The Role of Benevolent Sexism in Gender Inequality

Author: Jacqueline Yi

Website: https://wp.nyu.edu/steinhardt-appsych_opus/the-role-of-benevolent-sexism-in-gender-inequality/

General field: Social sciences, gender studies

The article distinguishes between hostile sexism and benevolent sexism. The author explains why benevolent sexism is still oppressive - it affects women's situation in the workplace, in relationships and their internal thought process. The author also mentions what can we do to fight benevolent sexism.
It's important to notice small, not-so-obvious, benevolent signs of gender inequality which are the reason why sexism is still a problem in today's society. By noticing and fighting benevolent sexism, we can minimize a problem of hostile sexism. Educating society about gender inequality is a key to fight it, which is why I strongly recommend reading the article and sharing gained knowledge with other people.
